# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PROJECT-LOCAL CONFIG MUST NEVER BE COMMITTED.
#
# hyperlane ships a GENERIC public engine. Everything project-specific (your
# paths, service launch commands, secrets, the assigned-lane registry, generated
# per-checkout env) is LOCAL to your machine and is ignored here. `hyperlane
# guard` (and the installed pre-commit hook) fail if any of these are tracked.
# See PROTECTION.md §2. Keep these patterns in sync with the guard in `hyperlane`.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Your real config (copied from hyperlane.conf.example) — paths + secrets.
hyperlane.conf

# Any project-local override / context, including a per-project CLAUDE.local.md.
*.local
*.local.*
/project.local/

# Machine-local lane registry (assigned offsets for multi-char checkouts).
.lanes

# Machine-local launch PID registry (Windows ownership substitute — maps each
# launched listener PID to its checkout, since Windows exposes no per-process cwd).
.lane-pids

# Generated per-checkout lane env (written into each checkout, but guard against
# a stray copy landing here too).
.lane.env

# Any shared local secret/key file.
.local-*

# Editor / OS noise
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.tmp
*.tmp.*
